  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A significant number of older people feel isolated and excluded from community life. PCDT supports older people who need help with gardens that they can no longer manage on their own. They are put in touch with other older people in the community who want to grow fruit and vegetables but do not have their own gardens or allotments. The project helps to reduce the loneliness and isolation of both groups of older people by bringing them together and both parties benefit from fresh produce, the chance to learn more about gardening and cooking as well as invitations to social events. Their all-round health and well-being is greatly improved as a result</narrative>
  </description>
